General.Name: One Media iP Group Plc
General.Description: One Media iP Group Plc engages in the acquisition and exploitation of mixed media intellectual property rights for distribution through the digital medium and traditional media outlets in the United Kingdom, rest of Europe, North America, and internationally. Its mixed media products include music, video, spoken word, and digital books. The company also provides third party licensing services; sync library that enables music supervisors and production makers to access, search, and review the library to find the music for the most exacting brief; technical copyright analysis tool, a software as a service platform for automating the time-consuming task of monitoring digital music releases; and Harmony IP, a music equity release platform. In addition, it manages audio and video content across a range of YouTube channels; and operates various online digital stores, as well as Point Classics catalogue, a library of classical music. Further, the company's music is used for synchronization in film, TV, and digital gaming. The company was formerly known as One Media Publishing Group Plc and changed its name to One Media iP Group Plc in October 2012. One Media iP Group Plc was founded in 2005 and is based in Iver Heath, the United Kingdom.
